In England, in the seven days to 09 February, there were 376,247 new confirmed cases (665.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 02 February, there were 531,873 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 29% (155,626 fewer cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 14 February is 15,648,433 (27,671.8 cases per 100,000 population).
